OL,3,GNorth East
OL,4,
OL,5,CThis Evening and Tonight:FWarm sunny
OL,6,Fspells will give way to a risk of rain
OL,7,Fand showers for a time, edging
OL,8,Feastwards. These showers may be heavy
OL,9,Fand thundery. Becoming generally drier
OL,10,Flater in the night. Mostly mild, but
OL,11,Fchilly in western rural areas.
OL,12,
OL,13,CSaturday:FBrightest early on, with
OL,14,Fsome warm sunny spells, although cloud
OL,15,Famounts generally increasing later.
OL,16,FMainly dry, although northern parts
OL,17,Fmay see isolated showers and perhaps
OL,18,Fthe odd rumble of thunder.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
